---

Wash and dry all produce. Bring a large #pot{} of salted water to a boil. Halve
@heirloom grape tomatoes{10%ounce} lengthwise. Mince or grate @garlic{2%cloves}.
Pick @tarragon{¼%ounce} leaves from stems, then chop until you have 1 TBSP.

Melt 1 TBSP @butter{2%tablespoon} in a large pan over medium heat. Add garlic and
cook until fragrant, ~{1-2%minutes}. Add tomatoes and cook until slightly softened,
~{2-3%minutes}. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Once water is boiling, add @lobster ravioli{9%ounce} to pot. Cook until they
are tender and float to the top, about ~{4%minutes}. Carefully scoop out and
reserve a few big splashes of ravioli cooking water, then drain.

While ravioli cook, rinse @shrimp{10%ounce}, then pat dry with a paper towel.
Add to pan with tomatoes. Cook until just barely pink, ~{2-3%minutes}. Season
with salt and pepper.

Add ravioli to pan with shrimp. Gently stir in @sour cream{4%tablespoon}, 1 TBSP
butter, and half the tarragon (use less to taste, if desired) and combine.
Season with salt and pepper.

> Add a splash or two of ravioli cooking water if sauce seems too thick.

Divide ravioli mixture between bowls. Garnish with remaining tarragon (to taste)
and serve.